5. Language Models

Definition:
Models trained to predict and generate text.

Goal:
Predict next word/token.

Examples:
- GPT
- BERT
- T5
- Llama

6. Tokens and Tokenization

Definition:
Breaking text into smaller units called tokens.

Example:

Sentence:

"I Love AI"

Tokens:

["I","Love","AI"]

Importance:
All LLMs work on tokens instead of words.

7. Embeddings

Definition:
Numerical vector representation of text.

Purpose:
Allow machines to understand semantic meaning.

Example:

King → Vector

Queen → Vector

Applications:
- Semantic Search
- RAG
- Recommendation Systems

